description: Number of labeled trimmed trees with n nodes.
comments: A trimmed tree is a tree with a forbidden limb of length 2.A tree with a forbidden limb of length k is a tree where the path from any leaf inward hits a branching node or another leaf within k steps.
links: Vincenzo Librandi, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..200
Index entries for sequences related to trees
formula: E.g.f.: 1 + x^3/2 + x^4/2 + B(x) - B(x)^2/2 where B(x) is e.g.f. of A052318.a(n) ~ (1+LambertW(-2*exp(-2)))^(3/2) * exp((n*LambertW(-2*exp(-2)))/2) * n^(n-2). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 29 2014
author: _Christian G. Bower_, Dec 15 1999
